  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> carrot[s]</strong> into thin batons</p><p>Chop your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> beef mince</strong> to a bowl with<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> ginger </strong>(save the rest for later!) and your <strong>beef stock mix</strong></p><p>Mix thoroughly until fully combined</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>beef mixture</strong> into 3 per person, roll into meatballs and flatten them slightly</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the meatballs to the pan and cook for 5 min on each side or until nicely browned</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> remaining chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped ginger</strong> in a bowl with your<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Once the meatballs are browned, reduce the heat to medium-high, add the<strong> sliced carrot</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 6 min or until starting to soften and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once soft, add your <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> and cook, uncovered, for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened, stirring frequently with a fork to separate the noodles</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>rice noodles</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> Vietnamese-style dressing</strong> to the pan along with the <strong>drained noodles</strong> and a splash of the<strong> reserved starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Mix well until everything is nicely coated in the dressing – these are your <strong>Vietnamese-style chilli beef meatball noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-chilli-beef-meatball-noodles/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Vietnamese-style chilli beef meatball noodles</strong> in a bowl garnished with the <strong>chopped peanuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
